  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>The Arrow represents the journey; the travels needed to reach a destination, through all factors of life. The Arrow's Folly depicts their failure, and the natural instinct to shy away from hardship to remarkable degrees.</p><p><strong>Constellation</strong> @UUID[Compendium.immortal-ardor.deities.Item.bQJ4eQKF50ofQdGr]{The Arrow}</p><hr /><p><strong>First Asterism </strong>(Level 1): You gain the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.Ux73dmoF8KnavyUD]{Fleet} general feat and you become Trained in Stealth. If you are naturally trained in Stealth, you can ignore difficult terrain while Sneaking.</p><p><strong>Second Asterism </strong>(Level 3, Trained in Stealth): You gain the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.fD9xjrnPfJ8aQxYA]{Keen Follower} general feat and you become an Expert in Stealth. If you are naturally an Expert in Stealth, you become @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.VRSef5y1LmL2Hkjf]{Undetected} if you successfully Hide.</p><p><strong>Third Asterism </strong>(Level 7, Trained in Stealth): You gain the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.Imvu2RV2ggjJ2HZt]{Swift Sneak} skill feat and you become a Master in Stealth. If you are naturally a Master in Stealth, you can Sneak and Hide in any form of Concealment or Lesser Cover.</p>"
